    .regular
      %h2
        %a{ :href => "http://tumble.toolmantim.com/post/54638434/using-any-font-with-imagemagick" }
          Using any font with imagemagick
      %p
        If you want to get Adobe font folio fonts, or any fonts really, working with
        %a{ :href => "http://www.imagemagick.org/" }
          imagemagick
        I suggest you skip the two hours of pain and simply do the following:
      %ol
        %li
          Download and install
          %a{ :href => "http://fontforge.sf.net/" }
            FontForge
          \.
        %li
          Use FontForge to save your font as a PS Type 1 into a directory somewhere. You should end up with a
          %code
            pfb
          and
          %code
            afm
          file.
        %li
          Use
          %code
            convert -list font
          to list the fonts on your system. The first line shows use the path to the XML file for your type definitions.
        %li
          Add an entry to that file for your font, pointing to the two files generated by FontForge.
        %li
          %code
            convert -font AkzidenzGroteskBE-Cn -pointsize 72 label:woot woot.png
      %p
        Tested on OSX but should work wherever.

  
